5.4 Understand __len__ and __getitem__
def __len__(self) -&gt; int:
    return len(self.features)
This tells PyTorch how many samples exist.
def __getitem__(self, index: int) -&gt; tuple[torch.Tensor, torch.Tensor]:
    return self.features[index], self.labels[index]
This tells PyTorch how to fetch one sample and its label.
The key idea is:
a dataset is not responsible for training. Its job is to deliver samples on demand.

6.4 Why Is forward() So Short?
def forward(self, x: torch.Tensor) -&gt; torch.Tensor:
    return self.network(x)
It is short because the structure has already been defined in nn.Sequential.
In more complex models, forward() gets longer, but the idea stays the same: it describes how data moves through the model.
